{"page": "Oblivion:Souls", "section_creatures": "1", "section_mapping": "3", "creatures_html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Souls_Alphabetically\">Souls Alphabetically</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Oblivion:Souls&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Souls Alphabetically\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>This table provides soul strengths for most of the <b>standard</b> creatures in Oblivion. Unique creatures (like the lich <a href=\"/wiki/Oblivion:Undead#Lorgren_Benirus\" title=\"Oblivion:Undead\">Lorgren Benirus</a>) generally have leveled souls that are not in this table.  See individual <a href=\"/wiki/Oblivion:Creatures\" title=\"Oblivion:Creatures\">creature</a> pages for full details on their souls.\n</p><p>Souls with a superscript (e.g., <sup>L:-1</sup>) are leveled; see the <a href=\"#Soul_Strengths\">later section</a> for details.  In a few cases (Ogres, Sanctified Spectre) there are several different versions of the creature sharing the same name but having different souls; see those creatures' pages for details.\n</p>\n<div style=\"display:inline-table\">\n<table class=\"sortable wikitable\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th style=\"width:15em\">Creature\n</th>\n<th style=\"width:6em\">Soul Level\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Oblivion:Ancient_Ghost\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Oblivion:Ancient Ghost\">Ancient Ghost</a></td>\n<td data-sort-value=\"3\">Common\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Oblivion:Black_Bear\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Oblivion:Black Bear\">Black Bear</a></td>\n<td data-sort-value=\"3\">Common\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Oblivion:Boar\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Oblivion:Boar\">Boar</a></td>\n<td data-sort-value=\"2\">Lesser\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Oblivion:Brown_Bear\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Oblivion:Brown Bear\">Br